	<tr>
		<td bgcolor="#DEDACB">
	
			<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
			Actually, I find this spell particularly useful for dealing with groups of monsters,<BR>
*especially* in places like Upper Guk.<BR>
<BR>
A correction to some of the information above is that it doesn't do 3 rounds of damage,<BR>
it does 1 to 3 rounds of damage, but at least it's area of coverage around the target is<BR>
around 10 to 15 feet.<BR>
<BR>
One caveat I will mention is that since this spell is a lot more<BR>
powerful than it's ice-based predecessor, you really, really, REALLY, want to make<BR>
cure you are a reasonable distance away from the monsters you cast this against,<BR>
because I while monsters may often resist it's effects, I have yet to see it fail<BR>
to do maximum damage against myself when I was being careless.
			</font>
	
